    <h1 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 20px 0;line-height:1.3;">What another org already figured out.</h1>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">Quick check-in. You signed up a few days ago and I wanted to send you one specific thing rather than a generic "how's it going" email.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">The real point of OTP is this: someone else already paid for the mistake you're about to make. If another org has published how their AI agents actually work, you get to read it and skip the six weeks of trial and error.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 24px 0;font-size:16px;"><strong>One thing worth 10 minutes this week:</strong> go to <a href="https://orgtp.com/browse" style="color:#0f766e;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">orgtp.com/browse</a> and read any OOS tagged with a use case close to yours. Even if the industry is different, the coordination patterns transfer. The way one agency structures agent handoffs is the same problem a law firm or a SaaS team is solving, just with different words.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">If you find one that changes how you'd build your next agent, reply to this email and tell me which one. I read everything.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 32px 0;font-size:16px;">-- David Steel, founder</p>

    <hr style="border:none;border-top:1px solid #e5e5e5;margin:32px 0;">

    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#777;margin:0 0 8px 0;">
      You're receiving this because you signed up at orgtp.com.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#777;margin:0;">
      <a href="<%- locals.unsubUrl || ('https://orgtp.com/api/v1/newsletter/unsubscribe/' + encodeURIComponent(email)) %>" style="color:#777;">Unsubscribe</a>
    </p>

